<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefdc478a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6111"><num value="6111">§ 6111.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefdc478b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6111/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such sums as are necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idefdc478c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s6111/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The funds so appropriated shall not be available for payment of the expenses or expenditures of the Council in administering any provision of an order issued under this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idefdc478d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/624/tXIX/s1932">Pub. L. 101–624, title XIX, § 1932</ref>, <date date="1990-11-28">Nov. 28, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3865">104 Stat. 3865</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
